    <item>
      <title>Winter&#39;s Heart</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/08/09/winters-heart/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 Aug 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/08/09/winters-heart/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;13891&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13891.winters-heart&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/winters-heart.jpg&#34;&gt;
                &lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A man who trusts everyone is a fool and a man who trusts no one is a fool. We are all fools if we live long enough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my opinion, entirely too much of &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;13891&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13891.winters-heart&#34;&gt; Winter&amp;#39;s Heart &lt;/a&gt; if taken up by Perrin attempting to rescue Faile and Elayne solidifying her grip on the Lion Throne. Either is an interesting enough plot line to carry for a little while, but they just go on and on&amp;hellip; I don&amp;rsquo;t think I&amp;rsquo;d mind if either was shortened significantly or even dropped entirely if/when the Wheel of Time goes to TV.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
